Proposed law generally retains present law but changes references from "gender" to "sex".
Proposed law defines "sex" as an individual's biological sex, either male or female, as
observed or clinically certified at birth. Gender identity and other subjective terms shall not
be used as synonyms or substitutes for sex.
Proposed law also authorizes and directs the La. State Law Institute to change all references
in law from gender to sex as it pertains to the personally identifiable information of an
individual.
Proposed law may be known and cited as the "Restoring Biological Truth Act".
